        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 5:19PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 518 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ramirez, or 15 miles west of Falfurrias, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Concepcion, Palito Blanco, La Gloria, Premont, Cruz Calle, Ramirez,
and Rios.

This includes US Highway 281 between mile markers 688 and 708.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
